modules.description: Provides functions to create, modify, and inspect byte arrays, including setting and getting individual bytes, slicing, and concatenating. Operates on mutable arrays of unsigned 8-bit integers. Used for efficient binary data manipulation in network protocols and file format parsing.

Provides operations to create and manipulate byte arrays, convert between strings and byte arrays, and perform memory-mapped reads. Works with Bigarray-based types for efficient low-level data handling, including 8-bit unsigned characters and 64-bit floats. Used for direct memory access in networking, file I/O, and binary data serialization.
